  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Manager, Planning",
  "description": "<p>Reporting to the Vice President of Planning, this role acts as a key liaison with our Head Office (HO) in Tokyo and will support in driving MSIG’s growth strategy across our business units in Asia (BUs) by planning, formulating, and reviewing strategies with a strong focus on corporate governance.</p><p><br />Responsibilities</p><ol><li>Strategic Planning & Performance Management: Lead strategic planning for the Asia region. Monitor and drive achievement of key financial targets (GWP, underwriting results, PAT). Ensure compliance with business excellence standards,</li><li>Business Expansion & Transformation: Drive initiatives to position MSIG as a market leader in Asia. Leverage digital technologies, promote synergy across BUs, and identify opportunities for M&A and strategic partnerships.</li><li>Corporate Governance: Continuously strengthen corporate governance practices for the Asia region. Oversee the arrangement and management of Board of Directors and Executive Committee meetings.</li><li>Reporting & Coordination: Deliver accurate and timely reporting to Head Office in Tokyo. Build and maintain strong relationships with the management team and relevant departments</li></ol><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Degree in Law</li><li>Minimum 8 years of experience in the general insurance industry, with experience in corporate planning and operations</li><li>Strong understanding of the general insurance industry, including political, social, and economic dynamics in Asia</li><li>Strong project management experience</li><li>Proficiency in written and spoken Japanese to communicate effectively with stakeholders and senior management at Head Office</li><li>Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills with a strategic mindset, financial acumen, and ability to collaborate effectively across multiple BUs</li></ul>",
